WorkItem.Description: This is concerning the warrior model.  Ok, i posted a issue before about a 245 item being higher than the 258 item on the dps scale, and i have found where the issue lies.  I can pull up my character, and go to the trinket page, and at one time the correct items are showing the dps they are suppose to, and then i'll click trinket again and the order will change.  Here is an example.  I'm on the trinket 2 list.  It is showing Death's Choice 245 as my second bis with my gear, and Deaths Choice 258 as my THIRD bis with my gear.  I go up to the drop down menu and click trinket 2 again, and it will actually change and Whispering fanged skull 251 will be my bis, and Deaths choice 245 will be my third.  Then i can go and click trinket 2 page again, and their order will once again change.  Not sure why this is happening, but i can now replicate the error. So there must be an issue.
WorkItem.Summary: [DPSWarr] Issue with trinkets and gear settings

Comments.Message:
Thanks for pointing this out.  It was due to a bug in the 2pc T10.  If you look at the value of the set bonus (buffs>set bonuses dropdown chart), you'll see that the set bonus was worth 200dps with the 245, and only 100dps with the 258.

Fixed for tonight's release
